# Riemann Hypothesis — Zero Verification
# ========================================
# All non-trivial zeros of zeta(s) have Re(s) = 1/2.
# Current record: 10^13 zeros verified on the critical line.
# Prize: $1,000,000 (Clay Mathematics Institute)
#
# Algorithm: Riemann-Siegel formula evaluates zeta(1/2 + it) at height t.
# Each zero is independent → embarrassingly parallel across t values.
#
# The computation:
# 1. For a range of t values, evaluate Z(t) (the Hardy Z-function)
# 2. Z(t) = exp(iθ(t)) · ζ(1/2 + it) — real-valued on the critical line
# 3. Sign changes in Z(t) indicate zeros
# 4. Verify each zero is ON the critical line (not off it)
#
# Z(t) via Riemann-Siegel:
#   Z(t) ≈ 2 Σ_{n=1}^{N} n^{-1/2} cos(θ(t) - t·ln(n)) + remainder
#   where N = floor(sqrt(t/(2π)))
#
# For t ~ 10^13: N ~ 10^6 terms per evaluation. Each evaluation is a reduce:
#   accumulate(1..N, All, "cos(theta - t*ln(n)) / sqrt(n)", Add)
#
# This IS a tambear accumulate. Kingdom A. Each t-value independent.
# 10^6 terms × 10^6 t-values = 10^12 operations. GPU in seconds.
#
# The .tbs dream:

read_range(t_start=3.0e12, t_end=3.1e12, step=0.001)
  .map(z_value = riemann_siegel_z(t))
  .scan(sign_changes)                    # prefix scan detecting sign flips
  .filter(is_sign_change)                # candidate zeros
  .map(refined_t = brent_root(z, t))     # refine zero location
  .map(verified = verify_on_critical_line(refined_t))
  .filter(verified == false)              # OFF the critical line??
  .collect()

# If empty: all zeros in this range are on the critical line. Record extended.
# If non-empty: RIEMANN HYPOTHESIS IS FALSE. $1M. Nobel equivalent.
# (But also: every zero ever computed has been on the line. 10^13 and counting.)
